  "prompt": "What can I do to be a good friend?",
  "response": "Being a good friend involves showing kindness, understanding, and support. Here are some ways to strengthen your friendships:\n\n1. **Listen Actively**: Pay attention and listen to your friend when they are talking. Show genuine interest in their thoughts and feelings.\n\n2. **Be Supportive**: Offer your support and encouragement. Celebrate their successes and provide comfort in difficult times.\n\n3. **Be Honest**: Share your thoughts and feelings openly but tactfully. Honest communication fosters trust and deeper connections.\n\n4. **Respect Boundaries**: Understand and respect your friend's personal space and boundaries. Everyone needs time to themselves occasionally.\n\n5. **Be Reliable**: Keep your promises and be dependable. Your friend should be able to count on you.\n\n6. **Show Appreciation**: Express your gratitude for their friendship, through words or small gestures.\n\n7. **Spend Quality Time**: Make an effort to spend time together. Shared experiences create lasting bonds.\n\n8. **Be Empathetic**: Try to understand things from your friend's perspective and show compassion.\n\n9. **Forgive Minor Mistakes**: Friendships may face occasional misunderstandings or conflicts. Be willing to forgive and work through these issues.\n\n10. **Offer Constructive Feedback**: If your friend seeks advice, provide helpful and constructive feedback rather than criticism.\n\n11. **Celebrate Their Achievements**: Recognize and celebrate their achievements, big or small. Show that you are genuinely happy for their successes.\n\nPracticing these behaviors consistently can help you become a better friend and deepen your relationships.",
